Annotation: the follow-up course in Tourism Finnish provides an in-depth coverage of issues of tour operation, destination management and types of travelling.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Objectives: to obtain Finnish language skills necessary in the tourism industry and aquire tourism terminology in Finnish.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) understands common spoken language, and have sufficient vocabulary to speak on tourism-related topics without preparation; 2) knows terminology in various fields of tourism and tour operation; 3) is fairly consistent and correct users of more frequent vocabulary and grammar items;  4) can compile and present presentations on tour operation; 5) can read and write business letters and others documents; 6) can communicate in service provision and sales situations; 7) can speak about tourism management and present sights in Estonia;  8) can use different publications and media in their work; (dictionaries, newspapers and magazines, internet; 10) understands importance of correct language usage in professional and business communication.
